Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{2} in half.
Peel and very finely chop the @garlic clove{2}. Finely chop your @red chilli{2}.

Toss the tomatoes in @salt{1/2%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}. Drizzle
over @olive oil{2%tsp} and the @balsamic vinegar{1.5}. Once they are totally coated
put them flat side up in a #baking tray{}. Roast on the middle shelf of the oven
for ~{20%minutes} then remove.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Tip in your @pine nuts{2} and toast
them (without oil) until they brown off.

> Watch them like you'd watch a toddler in a china shop - the moment you turn
> your back it could all go wrong!

Once the pine nuts are toasted remove them from the pan. Add @olive oil{1%tbsp}
to the pan, it should be really hot by now so lay in your @British chicken thighs{8}
skin-side down. Cook the chicken for ~{3%minutes} on one side to brown it off then
place on a baking tray, skin-side up. Grate a little @lemon{1} zest over the top
of the chicken and cook in the oven for ~{15%minutes}, or until cooked through
(keep the pan to save washing up!).

Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your pasta. Once rapidly
boiling add the @wheat spaghetti{360%g} and cook until 'al dente'.

Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to the pan you used for the chicken and place on
medium-low heat. Add the garlic and chilli (as much as you dare!) and season
with a pinch of salt and pepper, cook for ~{2%minutes}.

> Be careful not to burn the garlic.

When the spaghetti is ready, drain it and add to the pan with the garlic and
chilli. Add in the @wild rocket{1} together with the cherry tomatoes. Add
two thirds of the @parmesan cheese{3} and toss everything together.

Serve the spaghetti into #bowls{} and lay across some sliced chicken. Squeeze
over some lemon juice for a fresh touch and scatter on the pine nuts, remaining
parmesan, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.